      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNDER ANESTHETIC (7) goes very well at the distance with two wins and a placing from four starts. Missed the frame latest (18.29) when seventh over 300m at this track in a NG. With a clean break looks hard to beat. PAST TENSE (1) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (30.74) in a Grade 4/5 at Gunnedah. Solid record at the distance winning five races. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Expected to run well. STAR (2) missed the frame latest when sixth at Richmond (23.19) but was a winner five back in the best time of the program. Yet to win here but has run some good races. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Key runner on best form. CESSNOCK CURTAIN (4) is a last-start placegetter worth considering.",
